@startuml t_sequence_05_notes
title Sequence Diagram — Notes\n(note/rnote/hnote, left/right/over, spanning, color, multiline, across)

participant "Alice"  as A
participant "Bob"    as B
participant "Carol"  as C
participant "Dave"   as D
participant "Eve"    as E

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 1. POSITIONAL NOTES — note left of / note right of
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== note left of / note right of ==

A -> B : message one

note left of A : single-line note LEFT of A
note right of B : single-line note RIGHT of B

A -> B : message two

note left of A
    Multi-line note
    left of A
    three lines here
end note

note right of B
    Multi-line note
    right of B
    with **bold** text
    and //italic// text
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 2. NOTE OVER — single participant
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== note over (single) ==

A -> B : trigger note over

note over A : single-line over A

note over B
    Multi-line note
    over B
end note

note over C : note over C (not in message flow)

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 3. NOTE OVER — spanning two participants
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== note over spanning ==

A -> B : before spanning note

note over A,B : spanning A and B (single-line)

A -> C : wider span

note over A,C
    Spanning note over
    A, B, and C
    Multi-line spanning
end note

B -> D : even wider

note over B,D : spanning B through D

A -> E : full span

note over A,E
    Full span note
    covering all five participants
    A through E
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 4. NOTE ACROSS — full-width note
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== note across ==

A -> B : before across note

note across : single-line across (full width)

A -> C : another message

note across
    Multi-line across note
    spanning the entire diagram width
    regardless of participant count
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 5. COLORED NOTES  note #color
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== colored notes ==

A -> B : triggering colored notes

note left of A #FF8888 : red left note
note right of B #88FF88 : green right note
note over A #FFE0B2 : orange over note
note over B #E3F2FD : blue over note

note over A,B #E8F5E9
    Green spanning note
    with color applied
end note

note right of C #LightYellow
    Named color note
    on the right side
end note

note across #FCE4EC : pink across note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 6. RNOTE — rectangular note shape
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== rnote (rectangular) ==

A -> B : triggering rnotes

rnote left of A : rnote left (rectangular)
rnote right of B : rnote right (rectangular)
rnote over A : rnote over A
rnote over B
    rnote multi-line
    rectangular shape
    over B
end rnote

rnote over A,B : rnote spanning A,B
rnote over A,C #E3F2FD : colored rnote spanning

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 7. HNOTE — hexagonal note shape
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== hnote (hexagonal) ==

A -> B : triggering hnotes

hnote left of A : hnote left (hexagonal)
hnote right of B : hnote right (hexagonal)
hnote over A : hnote over A
hnote over B
    hnote multi-line
    hexagonal shape
    over B
end hnote

hnote over A,B : hnote spanning A,B
hnote over B,D #FFF3E0 : colored hnote spanning

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 8. CREOLE MARKUP INSIDE NOTES
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== creole in notes ==

A -> B : triggering creole-rich note

note over A,B
    **Bold text** in note
    //Italic text// in note
    ""Monospace"" in note
    --Strikethrough-- in note
    __Underline__ in note
    <color:red>Red text</color>
    <back:yellow>Highlighted</back>
    <size:14>Larger text</size>
    ====
    Horizontal rule
    ----
    Another rule
    * Bullet one
    * Bullet two
    ** Sub-bullet
    # Numbered one
    # Numbered two
end note

note right of E
    **Hyperlink in note:**
    [[http://example.com link]]
    [[http://example.com{tooltip} link]]
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 9. NOTES LINKED TO ARROWS (note on link)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== notes interleaved with messages ==

A -> B : first message
note right of B : immediate right note

B --> A : first response
note left of A : immediate left note

A -> C : second message
note over A,C
    Note spanning the
    just-sent message
end note

C --> A : second response

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 10. ENDNOTE / ENDRNOTE / ENDHNOTE (alternative end keywords)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

== endnote / endrnote / endhnote ==

A -> B : triggering alt end keywords

note over A
    Using endnote
    instead of end note
endnote

rnote over B
    Using endrnote
    instead of end rnote
endrnote

hnote over C
    Using endhnote
    instead of end hnote
endhnote

note right of D
    **Grammar targets (notes):**
    note left of ALIAS : text
    note right of ALIAS : text
    note over ALIAS : text
    note over A,B : spanning
    note across : full width
    note #color
    note over A\n...\nend note
    note over A\n...\nendnote
    rnote / end rnote / endrnote
    hnote / end hnote / endhnote
    Creole markup inside notes
    Colored notes (#RRGGBB, #name)
end note

@enduml
